    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi. Nos vir gloriosissimus
                            <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/186">Sicardus</persName>, Dei
                        providencia, Beneventane provincie <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>, per
                        <rs key="#Intercessory">rogum</rs> <persName key="#Other_palatine_officer #Intercessory" ref="#people/1905"
                            >Roffrid</persName>, <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">referendarii</rs>
                        nostri, concedimus in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots" ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Beati
                            Vincencii</orgName>, situm in Samnie finibus, super <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturnum</placeName>, ubi
                        venerabilis vir <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1903"
                            >Epyphanius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>, orator noster, preesse videtur, hoc est <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs> et <rs key="#Gualdi">vualdum</rs>,
                        posite in partibus <placeName key="#Forests #Gualdi #Roads #Common_land"
                            ref="#places/605">Liburie</placeName>, ubi dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Gualdi #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Roads #Common_land"
                            ref="#places/2351">Pantanu</placeName>, hos fines habentes: ab uno
                        latere via antiqua, que venit de Ducenta, et vualdum eiusdem monasterii,
                        quod ibi datum est a domno <persName key="#Gualdi #Marquis/duke"
                            ref="#people/158">Gysulfo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">duce</rs>, et quomodo perexit usque in ipsum
                        Pantanum, et <rs key="#Forests">silvam</rs> eiusdem monasterii; ex alio
                        latere via puplica, que vadit inter ipsum Maciana et Scarafena, et terra de
                            <rs key="#Rural_communities">hominibus</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Rural_communities" ref="#places/2801">Centora</placeName>, et sic
                        directe exit usque ad locum, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2805">Cree</placeName>, unde <rs key="#Rivers">aqua</rs>
                        exit, et sic directe intrat in ipsum <rs key="#Lakes">lacum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Lakes" ref="#places/701">Patriensem</placeName>; et ab uno
                        capite <rs key="#Roads">via puplica</rs>, que dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Roads">Vicana</placeName>, et pergit ad <placeName
                            ref="#places/2356">Cumas</placeName>; ab alio capite definit lacus
                        Patriensis. Hec autem terra et vualdu ideo in iam dictum cenobium concedimus
                        per iam dictos fines; seu concedimus atque firmamus, in eodem loco Liburie,
                            <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Gualdi #Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions #Roads #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Animals #Forests #Wood #Rivers #Riverbed #Other_basins #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1933">Sancti Sossii</orgName>; cum inclito
                        vualdo consistentes in iam dicto monasterio Sancti Vincencii, per ipsos
                        fines, qualiter datum est in prefato cenobio per sigillatum <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">preceptum</rs> a domno duce
                        Gysulfo, ut a modo et deinceps, per hoc nostrum roboratum preceptum, una cum
                            <rs key="#Other_basins">aquis</rs>, et <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, et pantanis, viis, et
                            <rs key="#Animals">pascuis</rs>, campis, et <rs key="#Forests #Wood"
                            >silvis</rs> et omnia infra ipsos fines manencia subter vel super, et
                        simul cum <rs key="#Riverbed">alveis</rs> et cursibus de ipso <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Riverbed">Laneo</placeName> et ipso <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Riverbed">Frigido</placeName>, iam dictus venerabilis
                        Epyphanius abbas et successores eiusdem monasterii firmiter et securiter
                        possideant in perpetuum, ita ut a nullis umquam potestatibus, vel
                        exactoribus, vel a quibuscuinque hominibus, nullis temporibus corrumpantur
                        aut removeantur, vel molestentur, sed perpetuis temporibus pars eiusdem
                        monasterii possideat. Quod vero preceptum firmitatis, ex iussione et
                        potestate, scripsi ego <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Radipertus"
                                >Radipertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>. Actum <placeName key="#Palatium"
                            ref="#places/110">Benevento</placeName>, in <rs key="#Palatium"
                            >palacio</rs>, primo anno principatus eius, mense februario, undecima
                        indiccione, feliciter. </ab>
                </div>
