            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This <foreign>praeceptum</foreign> was used as a source for the interpolation
                    concerning the Pantano forest in the Louis the Pious's diploma (CV I, no. 29, p.
                    233, footnote 1). It was included in the <foreign>Chronicon
                        Vulturnense</foreign> with some omissions and probably also some variants.
                    Vincenzo Federici assumes that in the original <foreign>praeceptum</foreign> the
                    donation of the Pantano forest was attributed to Ildebrandus, Duke of Spoleto,
                    who would be replaced here by Duke Gisulfus of Benevento.</p>
            </div>
